cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on video processing applications such as stereo VR video synthesis and 3D pose reconstruction.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper emphasizes the ability to scale to hundreds of machines.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with video analysis and processing.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant category as the paper mentions data-mining 70,000 hours of TV, which could involve the use of algorithms and data structures.
- cs.DB (Databases) is also a possibility as the paper deals with processing and analyzing large amounts of video data, which could involve the use of databases.
